Package org.neo4j.kernel.api

Interface KernelTransactionHandle

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    KernelTransactionImplementationHandle
    public interface KernelTransactionHandle
    View of a KernelTransaction that provides a limited set of actions against the transaction.

    • Method Detail

      • lastTransactionTimestampWhenStarted

        long lastTransactionTimestampWhenStarted()
        The timestamp of the last transaction that was committed to the store when the underlying transaction started.
        Returns:
        the timestamp value obtained with System.currentTimeMillis().

      • startTime

        long startTime()
        The start time of the underlying transaction. I.e. basically System.currentTimeMillis() when user called Kernel.beginTransaction(KernelTransaction.Type, LoginContext).
        Returns:
        the transaction start time.

      • startTimeNanos

        long startTimeNanos()
        The start time of the underlying transaction. This can be used to measure elapsed time in a safe way that is not affected by system time changes.
        Returns:
        nanoTime at the start of the transaction.

      • timeoutMillis

        long timeoutMillis()
        Underlying transaction specific timeout. In case if timeout is 0 - transaction does not have a timeout.
        Returns:
        transaction timeout in milliseconds, 0 in case if transaction does not have a timeout

      • isOpen

        boolean isOpen()
        Check if the underlying transaction is open.
        Returns:
        true if the underlying transaction KernelTransaction.close() was not called, false otherwise.

      • isClosing

        boolean isClosing()
        Check if the underlying transaction is closing. Closing means that the transaction is closed by the user and currently doing commit or rollback.
        Returns:
        true if the underlying transaction (KernelTransaction.close() is called, but not finished, false otherwise.

      • markForTermination

        boolean markForTermination​(Status reason)
        Mark the underlying transaction for termination.
        Parameters:
        reason - the reason for termination.
        Returns:
        true if the underlying transaction was marked for termination, false otherwise (when this handle represents an old transaction that has been closed).

      • subject

        AuthSubject subject()
        Security context of underlying transaction that transaction has when handle was created.
        Returns:
        underlying transaction security context

      • getMetaData

        Map<String,​Object> getMetaData()
        Metadata of underlying transaction that transaction has when handle was created.
        Returns:
        underlying transaction metadata

      • terminationReason

        Optional<Status> terminationReason()
        Transaction termination reason that transaction had when handle was created.
        Returns:
        transaction termination reason.

      • isUnderlyingTransaction

        boolean isUnderlyingTransaction​(KernelTransaction tx)
        Check if this handle points to the same underlying transaction as the given one.
        Parameters:
        tx - the expected transaction.
        Returns:
        true if this handle represents tx, false otherwise.

      • getUserTransactionId

        long getUserTransactionId()
        User transaction id of underlying transaction. User transaction id is a not negative long number. Should be unique across transactions.
        Returns:
        user transaction id

      • getUserTransactionName

        String getUserTransactionName()
        User transaction name of the underlying transaction. User transaction name consists of the name prefix and user transaction id. Should be unique across transactions.
        Returns:
        user transaction name

      • executingQuery

        Optional<ExecutingQuery> executingQuery()
        Query currently executing, if any, that use the underlying transaction

      • activeLocks

        Stream<ActiveLock> activeLocks()
        Returns:
        the lock requests granted for this transaction.

      • transactionStatistic

        TransactionExecutionStatistic transactionStatistic()
        Provide underlying transaction execution statistics. For example: elapsed time, allocated bytes etc
        Returns:
        transaction statistics projection

      • transactionInitialisationTrace

        TransactionInitializationTrace transactionInitialisationTrace()
        Provide stack trace of particular transaction initialisation call if that is available, empty record otherwise
        Returns:
        transaction initialization trace

      • clientInfo

        Optional<ClientConnectionInfo> clientInfo()
        Provide underlying transaction originator details
        Returns:
        transaction originator details

      • isSchemaTransaction

        boolean isSchemaTransaction()
        Returns:
        whether or not this transaction is a schema transaction. Type of transaction is decided on first write operation, be it data or schema operation.
